<hr /><div class="frontNewsItem odd"><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/fire2005/">ECS Fire</a></h3><p>Following the fire in the Mountbatten Building at the end of October, staff in the ECS Zepler Building will be returning to their offices on Monday 14 November, with postgraduate students returning on Tuesday, and undergraduate entry planned for Wednesday. There will be some constraints on our re-occupation of the building and these will be communicated to staff and students next week. Detailed planning is now taking place for the short and longer term.</p><p></p></div><div class="frontNewsItem even"><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/813">ECS Alumni Reception</a></h3><p>Around 120 graduates of the School attended a reception on Tuesday 22 November at the Institution of Electrical Engineers, Savoy Place, The Strand, London. The earlier graduate there was Howard Llewelyn, who graduated from University College Southampton (as it then was) in 1948, but all decades since then were represented, with some graduates flying from India, Switzerland, and Germany.</p></div><hr /><div class="frontNewsItem odd"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www2006.org"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_812_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=e5953d4894b90abd5ffaf8daf92b4fa9&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="" title="" border="0" width="120" height="62" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www2006.org">WWW2006 — Registration opens for 15th annual web conference</a></h3><p>Registration has now opened for the 15th annual World Wide Web conference which is being organized by the School of Electronics and Computer Science. WWW2006 is being held in Edinburgh from 23 to 26 May next year, the first time that this prestigious conference has been held in the UK. The conference delegates, who are expected to number around 1500, will include the world’s leading academics and researchers in the Web, as well as business leaders, industrial technologists, and key standards bodies attracted by the strong programme of keynote presentations.</p></div><div class="frontNewsItem even"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/808"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_808_img&amp;maxw=120&amp;maxh=120&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=9bbe38a68c8ae2af5ef7fc9c387004b0&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="" title="" border="0" width="83" height="120" class="thumbnail" /></a><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/808">Gathering of world’s experts in pattern analysis</a></h3><p>A workshop which will bring together the world’s top researchers in pattern analysis will take place this week. The Analysis of Patterns workshop, co-organized by Professor John Shawe-Taylor, Head of the ECS Information: Signals, Images and Systems group, will take place at the Centre Ettore Majorana for Scientific Culture in Erice, Italy from 28 October to 6 November 2005, and enable the world’s scientific communities committed to developing common principles of modern pattern analysis to come together and share their experiences.</p><p></p></div><p class="clearBoth"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051126011438/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/">More News</a></p><br style="clear: both;" />
